## SETUP & DEVELOPMENT

### Initial Setup
1. Install Node.js: https://nodejs.org/ (LTS version)
2. Install Vercel CLI: `npm install -g vercel`
3. Install project dependencies: `npm install`
4. Create `.env.local` file with Supabase credentials (see SUPABASE section)

### Run Development Server
```bash
cd C:\Users\viggo\code\lab-inventory
npm run dev
```
Then open: http://localhost:3000

### Python Environment (for Excel scripts)
```bash
# Create conda environment
conda create -n labinventory python=3.10
conda activate labinventory

# Install Python packages
pip install pandas openpyxl
```

### Upload to github and vercel
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2tQNI9NuBUo&t=149s
git remote -v
git remote remove origin
git remote add origin https://github.com/viggorey/lab-inventory.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

git add .
git commit -m "upload to repository"
git push


